# Database Configuration
# The memory system supports both SQLite (default) and PostgreSQL databases.
# Configure using either individual variables or a full DATABASE_URL.

# Option 1: Use DATABASE_URL (takes precedence over individual variables)
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///path/to/database.db
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:port/database

# Option 2: Use individual database variables
# For SQLite (default):
# DB_TYPE=sqlite
# DB_NAME=conversations.db

# For PostgreSQL:
# DB_TYPE=postgresql
# DB_HOST=localhost
# DB_PORT=5432
# DB_NAME=storyline
# DB_USER=postgres
# DB_PASSWORD=yourpassword

# If no database configuration is provided, defaults to SQLite with:
# - Database file: ./memory/conversations.db (contains both conversations and summaries)